  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To tackle this, deep learning methods based on neural networks (NNs) were employed.",
    "Such NNs could learn character and wordlevel representations, as well as sentence-level relationships, in their learning pipeline.",
    "Neural Network models tested Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) plus character embeddings and obtained an F1 score of 76.39, while a bi-directional long short-term memory (BiLSTM) character embedding approach achieved a 76.94 F1 score for a diseases dataset (Sahu & Anand, 2016).",
    "As with the general domain, BiLSTM-CRF (Conditional Random Field) models are popular in the biomedical domain (Cho & Lee, 2019; Li et al., 2019; Wang et al., 2019) with different combinations of character and word embeddings and features such as POS tags.",
    "Contextualised word representation based on transformers is the state of the art for many NLP tasks, and biomedical NER is no exception."
  ],
